%% Diagram: GFS-style read — client cache, master fallback, checksum verify
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant Client
    participant Cache as Client cache (LRU)
    participant Master
    participant CS1 as Closest CS
    participant CS2 as Alt CS

    Client->>Cache: 1. Lookup(file, chunkIndex)
    alt Cache hit (warm)
        Cache-->>Client: Locations + version (cached)
    else Cache miss
        Client->>Master: 2. GetChunkLocations(file, chunkIndex)
        Master-->>Client: ChunkInfo{replicas, version}
        Client->>Cache: Store (TTL 10 min)
    end

    Client->>CS1: 3. ReadChunk(handle, offset, len, version)
    CS1->>CS1: Verify CRC32C per 64 KB block
    alt OK
        CS1-->>Client: Bytes
    else Checksum mismatch / stale version
        CS1-->>Client: Error + report bad chunk to master
        Client->>CS2: 4. Retry on alt replica
        CS2-->>Client: Bytes
        Note over Master: Master schedules re-replication<br/>and version bump for the bad replica
    end
